        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "setupPlayerObservers"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method in this sample defines key-value observers on the player and player item properties. These observers enable or disable the fast forward and reverse buttons in the UI based on the reported values of the observed properties."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Play a Movie at its Natural Rate",
          "anchor": "3537250"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "togglePlay"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method toggles the playback state of the movie when the user taps the Play button in the UI. It first uses the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avplayer/1643485-timecontrolstatus"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property to determine whether playback is in progress or paused. If the player is paused, the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "togglePlay"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method initiates playback of the movie at its natural rate (1.0) by invoking the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avplayer/1386726-play"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method. If the player is already playing, the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "togglePlay"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method pauses playback by invoking the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avplayer/1387895-pause"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Perform Movie Scrubbing",
          "anchor": "3537251"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To handle movie scrubbing, this sample defines the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "timeSliderDidChange"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " action method on a slider control in the UI. Adjusting the slider control calls this method, which then sets the player time to the new value using the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avplayer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "  "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avplayer/1385953-seektotime"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method. The video corresponding to the new time is then rendered in the view."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "@IBAction func timeSliderDidChange(_ sender: UISlider) {",
            "    let newTime = CMTime(seconds: Double(sender.value), preferredTimescale: 600)",
            "    player.seek(to: newTime, toleranceBefore: .zero, toleranceAfter: .zero)",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "metadata": {
